nodes.title: Detailer (SEGS) Note
widgets_values:
## HAND SETTINGS: QUALITY FOCUS
- **Guide Size:** Set to **1024**.
- **Why:** This node uses **MeshGraphormer** (Depth/Pose), which is much lighter on VRAM than SAM. Your GPU can easily handle 1024px here.
- **Quality Impact:** **HIGH.** Hands consist of thin lines (fingers). Dropping to 512px blurs the joints, causing the detector to fail and producing "mangled" hands. High resolution is required for the math to work.

## HAND DETECTOR SETTINGS (MeshGraphormer)

### 1. Standard Res (1216 x 832)
- **threshold:** 0.50 (Standard confidence)
- **dilation:** 40 (Crucial! Adds width to prevent "Thin Noodle" crashes)
- **crop_factor:** 2.0 (Adds wrist/arm context for depth accuracy)
- **drop_size:** 40 (Ignores hands smaller than ~4% of image height)

### 2. High Res (3040 x 2080)
- **threshold:** 0.50
- **dilation:** 60 (Increased slightly for larger scale)
- **crop_factor:** 2.0 (Keep constant)
- **drop_size:** 120 (Scaled up. A 40px hand at this res is just noise; ignore it)

### 3. Detailer Settings (Constant)
- **Guide Size:** 1024 (Required for MeshGraphormer to see finger joints)
- **Denoise:** 0.40 (High enough to redraw bad geometry)
- **Feather:** 5 / **Mask Feather:** 20 (Blends the wrist seam)

## FACE DETECTOR SETTINGS (FaceDetailer)

### 1. Standard Res (1216 x 832)
- **bbox_threshold:** 0.50
- **bbox_dilation:** 10 (Faces are already square-ish, low dilation is fine)
- **bbox_crop_factor:** 1.5 - 2.0 (LOWER THIS! 3.0 is too big; it shrinks the face pixels)
- **drop_size:** 30 (Ignore tiny background faces)

### 2. High Res (3040 x 2080)
- **bbox_threshold:** 0.50
- **bbox_dilation:** 20
- **bbox_crop_factor:** 2.0
- **drop_size:** 100 (Scaled up. Fixes only the main character, ignores crowd noise)

### 3. Detailer Settings (Constant)
- **Guide Size:** 512 (CRITICAL! Prevents SAM VRAM crash. Face mask is simple shape.)
- **Denoise:** 0.10 - 0.25 (Low denoise preserves your "Graphite" texture)
- **SAM Threshold:** 0.93 (High precision for mask accuracy)
